AttributeList.Text: This function block handles all the logic for handling analog signals and alarms.

This network is used to scale the Analog Input Signal.
The logic checks that the ScaledValueMax is above the Minimum, And that the RawValueMax is above the Min. To avoid an error that could fault the PLC and stop it from running.
If the Input Type = 0, the INT is converted into a real and moved to the ScaledInputValue. If the Input Type = 10 and the ScalingInvalid = FALSE, then the value goes through the scaling process, and is moved into the ScaledInputValue.
Analog Scaling

This network is used to simulate the analog signal for testing purposes.
If the SimulationMode and GlobalSimulation = FALSE, then the ScaledValue is moved into the PVValue.
If either the SimulationMode or the GlobalSimulation = TRUE, then the scan that this is true, the ScaledInputValue is moved into the SimulationValue. The SimulationValue is then moved into the PVValue. The SimulationValue is adjusted from the HMI to Simulate a Value.
Analog Simulation

This network is used to enable or disable alarm latching for this analog signal.
The AlarmLatchEnabled is always TRUE. Meaning all alarms will latch.
Enable / Disable Latching

This network is used to enable or disable dock mode for each of the 4 Analog Alarms for this block.
If the DockModeEnable and the GlobalDockMode = TRUE, then the DockMode is enabled and = TRUE.
If either DockModeEnable or GlobalDockMode = FALSE, then the DockMode is disabled and = FALSE.
The same logic is repeated 4 times for each Alarm, HH-H-L-LL.
Dock Mode

This Network Enables and Disables the HHAlarm.
If the AlarmDisable or the DockModeEnabled = TRUE, then the AlarmDisabled = TRUE. (THE ALARM IS TURNED OFF AND WILL NOT ACTIVATE)
If either the AlarmDisable or the DockModeEnabled = FALSE, then the AlarmDisabled = FALSE. (THE ALARM IS TURNED ON AND WILL ACTIVATE.
High High Analog Alarm - Enabling and Disabling

This network sets the DelayTime for the Alarm.
If ExternalAlarm = TRUE, then 0 is moved into the DelayTime Variable. If ExternalAlarm = FALSE, then the DelayTime is set from the HMI.
DelayTime is multiplied by 1000, before being moved into the DelayTimer.PT, which is the Preset Variable for the DelayTimer.
High High Analog Alarm - Delay Time

This network monitors the Input value for the HHAlarm.
If PVValue is above the Limit, and the AlarmDisabled = FALSE, and the Qualifier = TRUE, then the DelayTimer begins timing. OR If AlarmActive = TRUE, and the PVValue is still greater then the Limit minus the deadband, the DelayTimer begins timing. OR If the ExternalAlarm = TRUE, the DelayTimer begins timing.
When the DelayTimer.Q (Output) = TRUE, then the AlarmActive is set to TRUE. If the AlarmLatchEnabled = TRUE, then AlarmLatch is also set to TRUE.
High High Analog Alarm - Monitoring for Alarm Condition

This network enables the HHAlarm Output.
If AlarmLatch or AlarmActive or AlarmTest = TRUE then Alarm = TRUE.
High High Analog Alarm - Alarm Active

This network contains the logic for the HHAcknowledge.
The first rung uses a Oneshot to stop the AlarmAcknowledge from being held = TRUE.
If AlarmLatch = TRUE and AlarmAcknowledge or Acknowledge = TRUE, then AlarmAcknowledged is set to TRUE.
If AlarmLatch = FALSE then AlarmAcknowledged is set to FALSE.
If AlarmAcknowledged and AlarmActive = FALSE, then AlarmLatch is set to FALSE.
High High Analog Alarm - Alarm Acknowledgement

This network contains the logic for the HHAlarm Horn.
If AlarmTest = TRUE, then the AlarmHornTest_Delay timer begins timing.
If the Severity is greater then 100, and Alarm = TRUE, and AlarmSilenced and Silence and AlarmHornTest.Q (Output) = FALSE, then the AlarmHorn = TRUE. OR If AlarmTest = TRUE, AlarmHorn = TRUE.
If Alarm = TRUE. and Silence or AlarmAcknowledged or Silence_MCR = TRUE, then AlarmSilenced is set to TRUE.
If the Severity is between 100 and 150, then 600 seconds is moved to the ReactivationDelayTimer.PT (Preset). If the Severity is between 150 and 200, then 120 seconds is moved to the ReactivationDelayTimer.PT (Preset). If the Severity is above 200, then 0 seconds is moved to the ReactivationDelayTimer.PT (Preset).
If Alarm and AlarmSilenced = TRUE, and AlarmSilenced_MCR = FALSE, the AlarmReactivationDelayTimer begins timing.
If Alarm = FALSE or AlarmReactivationDelay.Q (Output) = TRUE, then AlarmSilenced is reset to FALSE.
High High Analog Alarm - Alarm Horn

This network contains the logic for the HHAlarm Horn in the MCR.
If the Severity is greater then 100, and Alarm = TRUE, and AlarmSilenced_MCR and Silence_MCR = FALSE, then AlarmHorn_MCR = FALSE.
If Alarm = TRUE, and Silence_MCR or AlarmAcknowledged = TRUE, then AlarmSilenced_MCR is set to FALSE.
If Alarm = FALSE, then AlarmSilenced_MCR is reset to FALSE.
The AlarmHorn in the MCR does not have a reactivation delay, and cannot be silenced from outside the MCR. Once the alarm is silenced from the MCR, it is silenced permenantly until the alarm resets.
High High Analog Alarm - Alarm Horn MCR
